claim.claim-text:
A method of manufacturing a heat transfer plate (1C) where a heat medium pipe (16) configured to circulate a heat medium for heating or cooling a heat component is housed inside a plate-form base member (2), the method comprising the steps of

inserting the heat medium pipe (16) in a concave groove (8) open to an obverse (3) of the base member (2) and having a depth size longer than an outer diameter size of the heat medium pipe (16);

inserting a lid plate (10) in an opening (12a) of the concave groove (8) positioned at an upper portion of the heat medium pipe (16) within the concave groove (8);

deforming the heat medium pipe (16) plastically and making the heat medium pipe (16) abut with the concave groove (8) by pressing the lid plate (10) to a bottom portion (12b) of the concave groove (8); and then fixing the lid plate (10) to the base member (2) by friction stirring joining.
